Wash and dry all produce. Bring @water{2%cups} to a boil in a small #pot. Trim bottom root ends from @baby bok choy{4}(trimmed) and discard. Cut head in half lengthwise, then slice crosswise into strips. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{4%units}, keeping greens and whites separate. Peel, then mince @ginger{2%thumb}(minced) until you have 2 TBSP. Mince or grate @garlic{4%cloves}(minced).

Once water is boiling, add @jasmine rice{1%cup} to pot. Cover, lower heat, and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove from heat and keep covered until rest of meal is ready.

Combine @soy sauce{4%tbsp}, @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, @honey{8%tsp}, half the ginger, and half the garlic in a medium #bowl. Add @sirloin tips{16%oz} and toss to coat.

> TIP: If you have extra time, let beef marinate for up to 3 hours in the refrigerator.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef to pan, leaving excess marinade in bowl. Cook, tossing occasionally, until browned and almost cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Add scallion whites, remaining ginger, remaining garlic, and another drizzle of oil to same pan over medium heat. Cook, tossing, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Add bok choy and cook, tossing, until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Return beef to pan along with marinade from bowl. Let bubble until a thick sauce has formed, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between plates. Top with stir-fry. Sprinkle with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{2%tbsp} and serve.